This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of attention-based models, which are a popular technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve training and testing neural networks, which is a common task in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of bilingual context extensions, which could potentially involve techniques from neural network embeddings (cs.NE). Finally, the paper is based on translated movie subtitles, which could involve computer vision techniques for processing video data (cs.CV).
